mistral.reason: Il Politecnico mentioned in the context refers to two different entities - one being a cultural and literary magazine published between 1945 and 1947, and the other being the Politecnico di Milano, which is a university founded in 1863. Giulio Einaudi was indeed the publisher of the former Il Politecnico magazine, but he did not found it nor has any connection with the latter Politecnico di Milano.
